 East London - The Buffalo City Metro says it would like to thank and encourage the bravery of Mdantsane community members following a tip-off. "The City’s Law Enforcement and the Mdantsane Zone 1 SAPS on Monday arrested two suspects related to allegations of illegal electricity connections," the Metro said. "Following a complaint laid by the community, an investigation was undertaken and the mastermind behind connections was pointed out and arrested. "This also led to the arrest of a tyre business owner." The Metro said that both suspects would appear in court on Tuesday and charged under the criminal matters amendment act. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 